Subject: [PATCH 0/2] media: i2c: add Samsung S5K4H8 image sensor

Hi,

This series adds mainline support for the Samsung S5K4H8 8 megapixel
raw image sensor.

Hardware summary:
  - CCI / I2C control, MIPI CSI-2 4-lane @ 280 MHz (560 Mbps/lane)
  - External MCLK 24 MHz
  - Native array 3264x2448 SGRBG10; also 1632x1224 2x2 binning
  - Chip id 0x4088 @ register 0x0000

Register programming sequences are adapted from the Rockchip vendor
driver (GPL-2.0); register I/O uses mainline v4l2-cci. Stream on/off
writes the mode select register 0x0100 as an 8-bit value.

The driver uses the modern V4L2 subdev active-state API (init_state,
enable_streams / disable_streams, v4l2_subdev_init_finalize).

Tested on Motorola Moto E4 (perry / MSM8917) with mainline CAMSS +
libcamera: both this sensor (rear) and the existing OV5695 (front)
enumerate and capture (~24 fps full-res rear, ~17.6 fps front).

Series:
  1/2 dt-bindings: media: i2c: add Samsung S5K4H8 image sensor
  2/2 media: i2c: add Samsung S5K4H8 image sensor driver

Board DTS enablement is intentionally not included here and will be a
follow-up once the driver is accepted.

Please review.

Thanks,
Aneesh

